From: Mirko Montanari <mmontan2@illinois.edu>
Date: Tue, Mar 23, 2010 at 9:41=E2=80=AFAM
To: <jun.li@hp.com>


Dear Doctor Li,

I am a student of Prof. Roy Campbell at the University of Illinois at
Urbana-Champaign. Abhishek Verma forwarded me your message about the
possibility of a summer internship in HP with the focus of developing a
large-scale data management platform for enforcing data management policies=
.

My research experience is in the areas of security and distributed systems.
My current research is investigating the problem of large-scale
configuration management in data centers, with the goal of developing a
distributed platform for detecting configuration changes that lead to
violations of security policies. My research has a strong component of
distributed data-management and compliance checking, and I would be really
interested in working with your research team this summer.

Before starting my current project I developed several other systems for
distributed data management. I worked on the developed of a system for the
efficient dissemination of customized information in pub/sub systems, and I
also worked on the problem of dynamic replica management in the context of
sensor networks.

During my work I acquired an extensive hands-on experience on the J2EE
platform, web development, databases, and service-oriented computing. Given
my research interest in security, I am also very familiar with the concepts
of secure computing.

I find your research project very interesting and exciting, and I would be
really happy to get a chance to contribute. Attached you'll find my resume.

I am looking forward to hearing from you!
--
Mirko Montanari
University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign



---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: Li, Jun (HP Labs) <jun.li@hp.com>
Date: Mon, Mar 15, 2010 at 7:05 PM
Subject: could you forward my job description to the students in your team
and RE: Arrangement of phone interview for HPL summer internship position
To: Abhishek Verma <verma7@illinois.edu>


Hi Abhishek,

The internship position in our project is now re-opened again as the
student who accepted the offer two weeks ago decided not to come today.
Since your team at UIUC is working closely in the area of cloud computing,
will that be possible for you to forward the job description to the
students in your team or the sibling team in distributed computing, who has
reasearch backgrounds in this area and like to come to work at HP Labs in
this summer?

Thank you very much in advance!

Regards,

Jun

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D HPL Summer Internship
Position=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

In HP Labs at Palo Alto (http://www.hpl.hp.com/), we are currently seeking
qualified self-motivated MS and PhD students for the following intern
position in software and systems research.

This position is in the area of large-scale data management, with the focus
of developing a scalable platform as a cloud service to store and manage
data and enforce data management policies. This cloud service aims to help
service providers protect outsourced customer data and meet compliance
requirements. The involved data policies include data retention, data
availability, data integrity, data migration, and data access control,
among others.

This position requires deep knowledge and hands-on experience with
distributed systems and service-oriented computing, which include database,
transactional and parallel processing, high availability and fault
tolerance, and other related disciplines. This position also requires
strong object-oriented programming and web development skills (Java related
platforms preferred). Experience with Hadoop and Map/Reduce and knowledge
of secure computing (e.g., identity management, access control) are desired
but not required.  Qualified candidates must have excellent communication
skills and the ability to work independently and in a team. Please contact:
jun.li@hp.com, (650)857-4087.






From: vermaabhishekp@gmail.com [mailto:vermaabhishekp@gmail.com] On Behalf
Of Abhishek Verma
Sent: Monday, March 01, 2010 4:21 PM
